column4: I removed kde and some libraries accidently, how do I get those libraries back?
sudo apt-get kde* ?
sorry, sudo apt-get install kde*
But I don't want to install kde
what are you trying to do, I misunderstood then
Some applications don't work now after I removed kde, they worked fine before installing kde
some web applications
ok sudo apt-get build-dep name of package
you most have dumped some libs you needed
Yeah, but I don't know what I need
that's the problem
it should tell you
oh ok
if you know the name of the programs not working ie build-dep firefox
ok I have a problem,0 upgraded, 75 newly installed, 0 to remove and 0 not upgraded.
E: Package libsnmp10-dev has no installation candidate
E: Failed to process build dependencies
ok, seems high, but you may have removed some key libraries while removing kde
Might have, what should I do?
hit yes and install the 75 files
I can't that's the problem
explain, what happens?
that what I pasted
